According to the [[Book of Mormon]], '''Aminadi''' ({{IPAc-en|ə|ˈ|m|ɪ|n|ə|d|aɪ}})<ref>[http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/pronunciation?lang=eng LDS.org: "Book of Mormon Pronunciation Guide"] (retrieved 2012-02-25), [[Wikipedia:IPA for English|IPA]]-ified from «a-mĭn´a-dī»</ref> was a [[Nephite]]. Briefly mentioned in the [[Book of Alma]], he is a descendant of [[Nephi, son of Lehi|Nephi]], and an ancestor (through at least three generations) of [[Amulek]].  

During a speech to the people of [[Ammonihah]], Amulek states that Aminadi was known as a prophet that had "interpreted the writing which was upon the wall of the temple, which was written by the finger of God."<ref>[http://scriptures.lds.org/en/alma/10/2-3#2 Alma 10:2-3]</ref>

