{{BLP sources|date = January 2015}} {{Infobox Hindu leader| | name = Nirmalananda Swamiji | image = File:SriSriSri Nirmalanandanatha Swamiji.jpg<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Nirmalanandanatha Swamiji.png]] --> | birth_date = {{birth date |1969|07|20}}
| birth_place = CheeranaHalli, Gubbi Taluk, [[Tumkur]] District | guru = [[Shri Shri Shri Dr.Balagangadharanatha Mahaswamiji]] |philosophy =[[Natha Sampradaya]] | disciple = Millions of Students studied at Adichunchanagiri Educational Institutions and Crores of Devotees across the World. | honors = | literary_works =Chief Editor, Adichunchanagiri Monthly Magazine}}
'''Nirmalanandanatha Swamiji''' is the head of [[Adichunchanagiri]] Math.<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/hoping-that-these-blessings-convert-into-votes/article5859492.ece|title = Hoping that these blessings convert into votes|last = |first = |date = |work = |access-date = 22 January 2015|publisher = The Hindu}}</ref>
Nirmalanandanatha Swamiji was born as Nagraja on 20 July 1969, son of Shri Narsegowda and Smt Nanjamma, in a village called Cheernahalli in [[Gubbi]] taluk of [[Tumkur district]] in a Kannada Vokkaliga (ಒಕ್ಕಲಿಗ) Community .<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/305406/mtech-iit-mutt-head.html|title=MTech from IIT is mutt head|website=Deccan Herald}}</ref> After doing his Diploma at Government Polytechnic College (Tumkur), he did BE in civil engineering at [[National Institute of Engineering]] Mysuru and M.Tech in structural engineering at [[Indian Institute of Technology Madras]]. He was selected as a scientist at [[Central Water and Power Research Station]] Poona. He instead volunteered to teach at a blind school in [[Ramanagara district]]. In 1998 he renounced worldly life and became a Swamiji. [[Balagangadharanatha Swamiji]] appointed him as the head of the Adichunchanagiri Shakhe (branch) Matha at [[Chikkaballapura]].
When [[Balagangadharanatha Swamiji]] passed away on 13 January 2013, Nirmalanandanatha Swamiji succeeded him as head of [[Adichunchanagiri]] Matha.<ref>http://acmbgs.org/mahaswamiji-sri-nns/</ref>
